{
  "texts": [
    "Handcrafted features are utilized in conjunction with classical machine learning models for score prediction, and they can also serve as a complement to deep learning models (Uto et al. 2020; He et al. 2022).",
    "Representing essays using handcrafted features comes with its 1 3 own set of advantages and disadvantages.",
    "Handcrafted features employ interpretable models for predicting essay scores, making it easier to provide feedback to students compared to using black-box deep learning models.",
    "Furthermore, syntactic and lexical features can be employed for cross domain scoring tasks, as they offer domain independent context to the model.",
    "However, manually designing features can be costly, and these features are less portable."
  ]
}